Is it me, am I the drama? Said my pants to the tree as they competed for the spotlight 🤪 I’m just happy to be home for Christmas after 4 years.
#ChristmasInJamaica #Christmas2022 #FashionInspoDaily #BlackGirlFashion #BlackGirlsWhoBlog #BlackOwnedClothing #AmazonFashionFinds

Tell me about a time you revisited a familiar place and it felt brand new. I’ll go first. Traveling home and embarking on the “Joy Spence Appleton Estate Rum Experience “ with @chukkacaribbean did just that to me!
Jamaica is such dynamic island and there is always a new experience waiting for you just around the corner! 
This holiday, @chukkacaribbean gifted me the experience of venturing somewhere new at home. It was such a treat and I’ve been inspired to make this a tradition. With so many options to choose from, Chukka will be the first place I turn to plan my next adventure.
#BlackGirlsWhoTravel #BlackTravelGram #VacationInJamaica #JamaicaVacation

Thank you chapter one, hello chapter two! #JanuaryDump - leggooo

WHAT JANUARY FELT LIKE:
1. Planting seeds in new spaces
2. Letting go of what doesn’t serve me
3. Child like joy - (pictured my nephews, who I may or may not have bribed to take pictures 1&2 🥲)

WHAT JANUARY WAS: 
4. Nostalgia - Taco Night & Kalooki @ Will & Stines
5. My beloved bar cart - my current home design project. I’ve added some more things since this picture but what else should I get?
6. #WeGotFoodAtHome - Chef Khase with the Miso Ramen & Chili @beyondmeat 
7. Attending more PR events. Thank youu @ravixo for being my plus one 🥹. My ego used to tell me that these small wins aren’t worth celebrating but I am truly grateful and excited AF. Being in these spaces remind me that this is just the beginning of a beautiful journey AND there’s lot of work to do. 
8. Catching up with good friends (@lukethom) over good food @momoyasoho 
9. Hosting in our cozy home ♥️
10. January was beautiful and February is magical.

Hellooo #June. Cheers to the best month of the year (Im obviously biased). Cheers to the month where I turn my birthday into a lifestyle 😝. 

Whether you’re a June baby or not, I think we can all agree that June brings an enticing feel and warm energy. I’m ready for it all, are you?

I used to think I wanted it all but now I know that I absolutely only want what’s meant for me - the people, the places and the things that feed my soul. What’s for someone else can never be for me and vice versa. Tbh, I truly believe that when we’re intentional, we’ll land exactly where we’re supposed to be. 

- -

27 - You feel like magic already. I am stepping into this personal new year with a spirit of celebration. ✨

To know me is to know that I am a big birthday girl.

Not every day, month nor year feels this joyous. In fact, last year I didn’t even want to celebrate my birthday. That was the first and last time I’ll do that. My mom often says that we should always seek to live and not merely exist. & that’s exactly how I want to spend my days - celebrating life to the fullest. 

Thank you God for another year, for better health, more happiness and the discernment to grow into who you’ve always created me to be! 

P.S. One thing about @thebadsideof35, she gonna humble me lmao (slide 5😭)

My man my man? My fiancé My fiancéeeeee* 
Our love story will always be my favorite. Here’s to forever, I love you baby ♥️ ♾️

June was sweet and July will be even sweeter! 
- - 

The proposal dress 😍 When I bought this dress I knew it would be special but I had no idea just how special it would be. I wanted this dress sooo badly that I bought the only available size. It was two sizes larger so I had  get it tailored to fit me. I didn’t care how many people owned it or how popular it had become I needed it for myself.

Here’s a quick glimpse of my time in Tamarindo! While many of these excursions can be enjoyed in other countries, here are are some experiences that hit differently in Costa Rica:

* Surfing on the Pacific Coast 
* Outdoor Cocktail Market 
* Outdoor Concept Cafes like @potsandbowls 
* Ceviche! 
* Sunsets on Tamarindo Beach 

Ask me any questions about my time in Tamarindo!

During my recent Houston trip, I stayed at the @fshouston. There are a few standout features, in addition to the highly aesthetic lobby design, that make this @fshotels location worth revisiting 
1. Bandista - A modern speakeasy with Latin, carefully tucked behind a library-style art display 
2. Bathroom Lighting - The perfect mood lighting with an array of settings to choose from 
3. @Vivrelle showcase - A collection of designer bags for guest to rent for a complimentary 24 hour time period 
4. @Krigler Fragrance House - One of 9 locations throughout luxury hotels in the US. I think I found my dream wedding day fragrance here! 

#fshotels #fshouston

I know I’m not the only one whose timeline is split between “Summer ain’t over until September 23rd” and “Pumpkin Spice and Everything Nice” 😂. I don’t know about you, but I’m soaking up every last moment of the summer. Which side are you on? 

- - 
Regardless of the season, my favorite article of clothing is a dress (thanks, Mommy) and sundresses hit different. 💁🏽‍♀️ Now when it comes to a sundress, Imma give her some flare. You can easily take your sundress a level up with: 
• Earrings - Raffia style accessories complement tropical/floral prints and bright colors very well. This goes for earrings, bags and shoes 
• Bags - In addition to raffia material, woven, bamboo and basket style bags are the perfect summer staple 
• Shoes - When’s a better time to wear bright colored sandals than the summer? 

Sundress Season, Summer 2023 Style, Summer OOTD, Dress #SummerStyle #BlackFashionBlogger #ResortWear

These tailored trousers from @commense.official are one of my favorite fashion finds from 2023. They are staying with me in 2024 and the foreseeable future! 

✍🏽 Which of these (4) looks would you wear? Let me know in the comments below! 

👇🏽Tips for styling trousers
1. With heels & a “not so basic” basic top for an elevated look
2. With a pop of colour for a bold and playful look 
3. With casual elements (like a graphic or simple white tee) for style juxtaposition to create an edgier look. 
4. With a cropped top/jacket to highlight stylistic proportions and create a more visually interesting look.
